The 3rd edition, which kicked off last month, was an online competition. The competition, according to the Founder, Sandra Odige, was established to promote and shine the light on the face of the next generation of African Fashion and Lifestyle industry. The edition saw some of the most fashionable kids in the country engaging in keenly contested weekly tasks and activities for the face of La Mode Kid of The Year 2022 and becoming the face of the next generation of African fashion and lifestyle.   ‘Men who love ladies with big backsides are chronic…     Davido creates legacy in new film for Martell     Anita Joseph criticises Nollywood ghost scenes   The competition, which ended on May1, saw Denzel Essien emerge as the winner with Paula Chideraodsigo T. Kenneth and the adorable Aviela Attahiru emerging as the 1st and second runners up respectively. Winners are set to win lots of amazing prizes, including a cash prize of N500,000, a cover and special interview features on the prestigious La Mode magazine, a special recognition award at the La Mode Magazine Green October Event 2022 “La Mode Kid of the year award recognition”, Walk the runway at the Green October Event 2022, massive media exposure, Special styling by top kids fashion brands, Special recognition awards, endorsement deals and so much more.